    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>A deactivating group attached to a benzene ring reduces the electron density within the ring, thereby slowing down and complicating electrophilic aromatic substitution reactions compared to reactions with benzene alone.</p>\n<p>In the given list, the following are deactivating groups:</p>\n\n<p><p>$-\\mathrm{Cl}$</p></p>\n<p><p>$-\\mathrm{SO}_3\\mathrm{H}$</p></p>\n<p><p>$-\\mathrm{COOCH}_3$</p></p>\n\n<p>These groups withdraw electron density from the benzene ring, making it less reactive to electrophiles.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "ap-eapcet-2024-21th-may-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
