    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Identify the ortho and para-directing groups towards aromatic electrophilic substitution reactions from the following list</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{\\mathop { - OH}\\limits_I \\mathop { - CN}\\limits_{II} \\mathop { - C{O_2}H}\\limits_{III} \\mathop { - OC{H_3}}\\limits_{IV} \\mathop { - NHCOC{H_3}}\\limits_V \\mathop { - CHO}\\limits_{VI}}$$</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "I, IV, V"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "II, III, VI"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "I, II, IV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "IV, V, VI"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Electron rich groups act as ortho and para directing groups as they increases electron density at these two positions.</p>\n<p>Out of the given groups, following are electron rich and deficient,</p>\n<p>Electron rich $$-\\mathrm{OH},-\\mathrm{OCH}_3,-\\mathrm{NHCOCH}_3$$</p>\n<p>Electron deficient $$-\\mathrm{CN},-\\mathrm{CO}_2 \\mathrm{H},-\\mathrm{CHO}$$</p>\n<p>Hence, $$-\\mathrm{OH},-\\mathrm{OCH}_3$$ and $$-\\mathrm{NHCOCH}_3$$ acts as ortho and para-directing groups towards electrophilic substitution reactions.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "ap-eapcet-2022-4th-july-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
