  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Arrange the following in decreasing order of their pK<sub>b</sub> values</p>\n<p>A. ,$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{NH}_2$$</p>\n<p>B. $$(\\mathrm{CH}_3)_3 \\mathrm{~N}$$</p>\n<p>C. <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyn4a8gq/060c527b-ab0f-4981-b594-a45ebaba7c47/c0ec6490-42bb-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4a8gr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyn4a8gq/060c527b-ab0f-4981-b594-a45ebaba7c47/c0ec6490-42bb-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4a8gr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2022 - 4th July Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 14 English 1\"></p>\n<p>D. <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyn4api3/f06bb31b-09fc-40b9-a7b9-4b7e8f055fae/ce15d6b0-42bb-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4api4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyn4api3/f06bb31b-09fc-40b9-a7b9-4b7e8f055fae/ce15d6b0-42bb-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4api4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2022 - 4th July Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 14 English 2\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "D > A > C > B"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "A > B > D > C"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "D > C > B > A"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "A > C > D > B"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$\\mathrm{p} K_b \\propto \\frac{1}{\\text { Basicity }}$$</p>\n<p>$$A$$ and $$B$$ are more basic than $$C$$ and $$D$$ due to $$+I$$-effect of methyl group $$A$$ which is more basic than $$B$$. This is because of high/more steric hindrance in $$B$$ due to three methyl groups. Out of $$C$$ and $$D, C$$ is more basic than $$D$$ because of more steric hindrance in $$B$$. So, order of basicity is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyn4dbn1/c28c3964-6c21-4586-b0f2-fe157d2e2100/16cdddd0-42bc-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4dbn2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyn4dbn1/c28c3964-6c21-4586-b0f2-fe157d2e2100/16cdddd0-42bc-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4dbn2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2022 - 4th July Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 14 English Explanation 1\"></p><p>Thus, decreasing pK<sub>b</sub> order of given compounds is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyn4e5ex/ab8b7f19-8c59-4f21-8138-5fa2aebe62fc/2dcded90-42bc-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4e5ey.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyn4e5ex/ab8b7f19-8c59-4f21-8138-5fa2aebe62fc/2dcded90-42bc-11ef-88a4-49982ab83277/file-jaoe38c1lyn4e5ey.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2022 - 4th July Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 14 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>i.e. D &gt; C &gt; B &gt; A.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "ap-eapcet-2022-4th-july-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
