  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which of the following is not explained by hyperconjugation?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Stability order of carbanions\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Stability order of free radicals\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Stability order of carbocations\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Stability of alkenes"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Hyperconjugation is a stabilising interaction\nbetween one or more $$\\sigma$$-bonds and one or more $$\\pi$$-bonds.</p>\n<p>It helps in explaining stability order of free\nradicals, carbocations, alkanes but cannot explain\nstability of carbanion due to presence of vacant\norbitals.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "ap-eapcet-2021-20th-august-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
