    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ly9tzyqz/a4f1c540-6c13-4bc6-ac16-ace43bb2ed3f/579807b0-3b6d-11ef-9b9d-75eda371a206/file-jaoe38c1ly9tzyr0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ly9tzyqz/a4f1c540-6c13-4bc6-ac16-ace43bb2ed3f/579807b0-3b6d-11ef-9b9d-75eda371a206/file-jaoe38c1ly9tzyr0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2021 - 20th August Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 17 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>According to Markownikov rule, in addition\nreaction of unsymmetrical alkenes, electron rich\ncomponent of reagent add to carbon atom with\nfewer hydrogen atoms bonded to it.</p>",
