    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The complete shifting of $$\\pi$$-electron pair of a\nmultiple bond to one of the bonded atoms in\npresence of the attacking reagents is called\nelectromeric effect.</p>\n<p>Positive electromeric effect (+E)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ly4ejl7p/9c42c0dc-3d20-4752-9893-012a526452c8/fc01e550-3870-11ef-bfd7-bb5215d9b1c1/file-jaoe38c1ly4ejl7q.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ly4ejl7p/9c42c0dc-3d20-4752-9893-012a526452c8/fc01e550-3870-11ef-bfd7-bb5215d9b1c1/file-jaoe38c1ly4ejl7q.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2021 - 19th August Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 19 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Negative electromeric effect [$$-$$E]</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ly4ek3vi/419168dd-7dcf-4a89-97c4-321a21f6c1ed/0a6c3be0-3871-11ef-bfd7-bb5215d9b1c1/file-jaoe38c1ly4ek3vj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ly4ek3vi/419168dd-7dcf-4a89-97c4-321a21f6c1ed/0a6c3be0-3871-11ef-bfd7-bb5215d9b1c1/file-jaoe38c1ly4ek3vj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AP EAPCET 2021 - 19th August Morning Shift Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 19 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>In positive $$+$$E effect, $$\\pi$$-electrons of the multiple\nbonds are transfered to that atom to which the\nreagent gets attached.</p>\n<p>In negative $$-$$E effect, $$\\pi$$-electrons of the multiple\nbonds are transferred to that atom to which the\nattacking reagent does not get attached.</p>",
